Could you add a comment on the above method on why we skip the noon - 12 hours calculation here. Comment:
// In OTP LocalDate is sometimes used to represent ServiceDate. This calculation is "safe" because 
// calculations on LocalDate ignore TimeZone adjustments, just like the ServiceDate. So, in this case it is not 
// necessary to: 'NOON - 12 hours + secondsSinceStartOfDay'

This method would also be clearer if the variable names was serviceDate and serviceTimeInSeconds. To me the secondsSinceStartOfDay means midnight, which is not true given a time-zone and DST switch.

