timeline.bodyText:
I do not think this is correct. I had to write a little test to verify it:
ZoneId fi = ZoneId.of("Europe/Helsinki");
ZoneId no = ZoneId.of("Europe/Oslo");
ZonedDateTime t0 = ZonedDateTime.of(2020, 11, 1, 0, 20, 0,0, fi);
ZonedDateTime t1 = ZonedDateTime.of(2020, 11, 1, 1, 20, 0,0, fi);
System.out.println(TimeUtils.timeToStrShort(secondsSinceStartOfService(t0, t0, no)));
System.out.println(TimeUtils.timeToStrShort(secondsSinceStartOfService(t1, t1, no)));
$ 23:20
$ 00:20

The Netex import uses the "raw" local date of the xsd:Date passed in as the service date. The SiriTimetableSnapshotSource seems to use the first estimated call and the "raw" date from that.
One problem here is that for input times with time-zone ahead of the graph timezone we may get negative time offset, assuming we use the "raw" date. The other option is to move the service date to the day before, but that is very confusing. So, I am in favor of using the "raw" date and then risk negative times.

